                <h2>The State of IT Cybersecurity in Oman</h2>
                <p>In recent years, Oman has made significant strides in bolstering its IT cybersecurity infrastructure. With a growing number of digital platforms, the need to protect sensitive data has never been more critical. This article explores the current trends and challenges in IT security across various sectors in Oman.</p>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h2>Operational Technology (OT) Cybersecurity: Unique Challenges in Oman</h2>
                <p>While IT cybersecurity focuses on protecting data, OT cybersecurity ensures the safety and integrity of physical systems, such as industrial control systems. In Oman, where industries like oil & gas are critical, securing these systems is vital to national infrastructure. This article discusses the specific challenges and solutions for OT cybersecurity in the country.</p>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h2>Emerging Cyber Threats in Oman: What You Need to Know</h2>
                <p>As cyber threats evolve, Oman is no exception to the rising challenges. From ransomware to advanced persistent threats (APTs), this article covers the latest trends and what organizations in Oman should be aware of to mitigate risks effectively.</p>
            </article>
